Rating: 4
I have served this a couple of times and although it is a labour of love, it is better when the pit is removed and they are roughly chopped...easier to spread. So even though I try to get a good variety without pits, sometimes I have to remove some pits but it is worth it. I have also added some whole garlic cloves to the mixture and cook them a bit longer than the olives, they are a delicious addition.

