Wow! Seems like a "Duh" combination and I am jealous I didn't think of it first! But Wow! This is such a great presentation. I served it with Camembert. However, any similar cheese would work. I used a combination of cured and marinated olives from a fresh market olive bar but did go through the effort of warming the oil, olives, thin lemon slices and herbs. Not sure it was necessary, however, it was nice to have it slightly warm. I served it with artisan style baguette slices drizzled with olive oil and rubbed with garlic. (what can I say?? I had some extra time!) My goal was to provide a tasty, savory appetizer course at an intimate dinner party. The saltiness, full flavors and the cheese really stimulated appetites! Served with a Shiraz from Argentina! Excellent!

